# Design System Rules

## Color Tokens

Always use CSS variables from [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) instead of hardcoded colors:

**✅ DO:**

```tsx
className = "bg-primary text-primary-foreground";
className = "border-border";
className = "text-muted-foreground";
```

**❌ DON'T:**

```tsx
className = "bg-[#ff9c0d]";
className = "text-[#ffffff]";
```

## Spacing & Layout

Use predefined spacing tokens from CSS variables:

- `--space-1` to `--space-16` → `p-1`, `p-2`, `p-4`, `p-6`, `p-8`, `p-12`, `p-16`
- `--radius-*` → `rounded-sm`, `rounded-md`, `rounded-lg`, `rounded-xl`

## Component Variants

Use [class-variance-authority (CVA)](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx) for component variants:

```tsx
const variants = cva("base-classes", {
  variants: {
    variant: { primary: "bg-primary", secondary: "bg-secondary" },
    size: { sm: "h-9 px-3", md: "h-10 px-4", lg: "h-11 px-8" },
  },
});
```

## Utility Functions

Always use the `cn()` utility from [src/lib/cn.ts](mdc:src/lib/cn.ts) for merging classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/cn";
className={cn("base-classes", conditional && "conditional-classes")}
```

## Gaming Theme

This is a gaming app with dark theme. Use gaming-specific colors:

- `gaming-bg`, `gaming-card`, `gaming-gold`, `gaming-dark`
- Orange accent color (`--color-primary: 255 156 13`)
